===2020 census===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Garey had a population of 72. The population density was {{convert|56.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Garey was 55 (76%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (1%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 5 (7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 10 (14%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 18 persons (25%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Garey CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0629070 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 27 households, out of which 8 (30%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 14 (52%) were married-couple households, 1 (4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 7 (26%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 5 (19%) had a male householder with no partner present. 5 households (19%) were one person, and 1 (4%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.67.<ref name=DP1/> There were 19 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (70% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Garey CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0629070 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 13 people (18%) under the age of 18, 9 people (13%) aged 18 to 24, 10 people (14%) aged 25 to 44, 26 people (36%) aged 45 to 64, and 14 people (19%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 48.0{{nbsp}}years. There were 27 males and 45 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 33 housing units at an average density of {{convert|26.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 27 (82%) were occupied. Of these, 17 (63%) were owner-occupied, and 10 (37%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

